handist.collections.function

Interface LongTBiConsumer<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of the object used as second parameter
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SerializableLongTBiConsumer<T>

    public interface LongTBiConsumer<T>
    Functional interface for actions taking a long and a generic type T as parameter. This is used to perform actions on RangedLists where the long index and the element are used.

    This interface removes the boxing and un-boxing operations that would otherwise occur when using the standard BiConsumer with types Long and T as generic parameter types.
